OL,3,CSunak's Sambas: PM offers apology
OL,4,Cafter 'ruining credibility' of shoe
OL,6,FBritish GQ magazine said that "in a
OL,7,Fbid to present himself as young and
OL,8,Fhip, Rishi Sunak took an eternally
OL,9,Fcool sneaker and ruined it for
OL,10,Feveryone", while footwear historian
OL,11,FElizabeth Semmelhack told The Times it
OL,12,Fcould prove to be "the death knell"
OL,13,Ffor the retro trainer.
OL,15,FMr Sunak told LBC Radio: "I issue a
OL,16,Ffulsome apology to the Samba
OL,17,Fcommunity. But, in my defence, I would
OL,18,Fsay I have been wearing Adidas
OL,19,Ftrainers including Sambas ` and
OL,20,Fothers, in fact ` for many, many years.
